{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in French Guiana", "text_new": "{{distinguish|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Guyana}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in French Guiana, France}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in French Guiana\n| map1 = File:Covid french guiana-2020-04-12.png\n| places = \n| legend1 = Districts with one or more cases\n| map2 = \n| legend2 =\n| map3 =\n| legend3 =\n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[French Guiana]]\n| first_case = [[Saint-Laurent-du-Maroni]]\n| arrival_date = 4 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=4|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = [[France]]\n| confirmed_cases = 88 <ref name=\"upd-04-13\"/> (2020-04-13)\n| suspected_cases =\n| recovery_cases = 53\n| deaths = 0\n| total_ili =\n| website = [http://www.guyane.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/Coronavirus-Covid-19/COVID-INFO COVID-INFO]\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] has reached the French [[overseas department and region]] of [[French Guiana]].\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n===March===\nOn 4 March, [[French Guiana]] had five confirmed cases of [[COVID-19]], all in [[Saint-Laurent du Maroni]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.antiguaobserver.com/five-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-french-guiana-march-4-2020/ |title=Five coronavirus cases confirmed in French Guiana March 4, 2020 |website=Antigua Observer |date=4 March 2020 |accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March, [[Guiana Space Center]] has suspended launch activities. <ref name=\"arienespace\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.arianespace.com/press-release/covid-19-guiana-space-center-suspends-launch-campaigns/|title=COVID-19: Guiana Space Center suspends launch campaigns|website=Ariane Space|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, the following measure were announced by the [[Emmanuel Macron|President of the Republic]]: It is prohibited to leave the house except for essential journeys which includes: shopping for food, travelling to work, accessing healthcare, and exercising within 1 km of the household. <ref name=\"travel\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.guyane.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/Coronavirus-Covid-19/COVID-19-Informations/Mesures-de-restriction-de-circulation|title=Mesures de restriction de circulation |language=fr|website=guayne.gouv.fr|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, all air travel for passengers will be halted from midnight onwards. <ref name=\"airport\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/politique/les-deplacements-aeriens-en-outre-mer-officiellement-interdits-jusqu-au-15-avril-466935.php|title=Les d\u00e9placements a\u00e9riens en outre-mer officiellement interdits jusqu'au 15 avril|language=fr|website=France-Guyane|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, [[Marc Del Grande]], the [[List of colonial and departmental heads of French Guiana|Prefect]] of French Guiana, instituted a curfew in [[Cayenne]] from 20:00 and 21:00 elsewhere. <ref name=\"curfew\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/politique/covid-19-il-faut-preparer-la-guyane-a-affronter-un-pic-important-466992.php|title=Covid-19: \"We must prepare Guyana to face an important peak\"|website=France-Guyane|language=fr|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===April===\n\nOn 4 April, a laboratory assistant from Andr\u00e9e-Rosemon Hospital Center tested positive. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/sante/coronavirus/covid-19-la-guyane-desormais-en-stade-2-de-l-epidemie-467153.php|title=Covid 19: Guiana is now in stage 2 of the epidemic|language=fr|website=France-Guyane|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 April, there were 77 cases and 34 recoveries. The districts affected are Saint-Laurent, [[Kourou]], [[Cayenne]] and [[Maripasoula]] <ref name=\"upd_04-07\">{{cite web|title=Covid Info du mardi 7 avril 2020|language=fr|url=http://www.guyane.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/Coronavirus-Covid-19/COVID-INFO/Covid-Info-du-mardi-7-avril-2020|website=www.guyane.gouv.fr|accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref> Groupe Bernard Hayot has donated 1,300,000 masks for free to health works in [[Martinique]], [[Gaudeloupe]], Guiana, and [[R\u00e9union]] <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/sante/coronavirus/le-groupe-bernard-hayot-fournit-1-3-million-de-masques-aux-soignants-467251.php|title=Groupe Bernard Hayot group donated 1.3 million masks to health workers (in French)|access-date=9 April 2020|website=France-Guyane}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April 2020, the [[European Union]] announced a grant of \u20ac8M (US$8.6M), which will be implemented by the [[Caribbean Public Health Agency]], for the fight against the Corona virus. French Guiana is one of the 24 members of the CARPHA. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.kaieteurnewsonline.com/2020/04/09/eu-provides-us8-6m-grant-for-cbean-to-combat-covid-19/|title=\nEU provides US$8.6M grant for C\u2019bean to combat COVID-19|website=Kaieteur News|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref> \n<br>\nA cluster of 13 cases has been located at the [[Indigenous peoples|indigenous]] village C\u00e9cilia in [[Matoury]]. 13 out of 16 suspected cases have tested positive. The Prefect  has ordered a confinement of the village. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/sante/coronavirus/13-cas-confirmes-dans-un-village-amerindien-a-matoury-467330.php|title=13 cases confirmed in an Amerindian in Matoury|language=fr|website=France-Guyane|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref> \n\nOn 10 April 2020, the report of the Scientific Council on the Evolution of the Coronavirus in the Overseas Territories has been released which calls for strict confinement, doubling of hospital capactity. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/coronavirus-le-conseil-scientifique-craint-une-aggravation-de-la-situation-outre-mer-et-preconise-le-maintien-strict-du-confinement-821800.html|title=Coronavirus: the scientific council fears a worsening of the Overseas situation and recommends \"the strict maintenance of confinement\"|language=fr|access-date=12 April 2020|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re}}</ref> ARS Guyane replied on 13 April that they will apply certain recommendations, but also stated that the number of ICU beds had been increased to 38 and is sufficient at moment given that there are currently no people on ICU. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guyane/coronavirus-certaines-recommandations-du-conseil-scientifique-pour-l-outre-mer-seront-appliquees-en-guyane-822546.html|title=Coronavirus : certaines recommandations du conseil scientifique pour l\u2019outre-mer seront appliqu\u00e9es en Guyane|language=fr|access-date=14 April 2020|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 April 2020, France and [[Suriname]] announced joint efforts to prevent illegal crossings of the [[Maroni (river)|Maroni]] river separating Suriname and French Guiana, <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.waterkant.net/suriname/2020/04/11/maatregelen-suriname-en-frankrijk-bij-grens-ter-bestrijding-van-coronavirus/|title=Measures Suriname and France at border to prevent Coronavirus |language=nl|website=Waterkant|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> and established a contact point in [[Saint-Laurent-du-Maroni]] and [[Albina, Suriname|Albina]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deboodschap.today/gezamenlijke-persverklaring-suriname-en-frankrijk-in-het-kader-van-maatregelen-bij-de-grensrivier-ter-bestrijding-van-covid-19-in-het-marowijne-bekken/|title=Joint Press Statement Suriname and France regarding measures at border river in order to prevent Covid 19 in the Maroni area|language=nl|access-date=11 April 2020|website=Nationaal Informatie Instituut De Boodschap}}</ref> On 13 April, the [[Marc Del Grande|Prefect]] mobilised the army to guard the river for its entire length. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.starnieuws.com/index.php/welcome/index/nieuwsitem/58105|title=French ambassador: Border of 520 kilometres is a challenge (in Dutch)|website=Star Nieuws|access-date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 April 2020, Dr. Hatem Kallel announced that the patient who had been in [[Intensive care unit|ICU]] since 2 April has been discharged. There are currently no patients in intensive care. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/sante/coronavirus/covid-19-l-unique-patient-en-reanimation-est-sorti-aujourd-hui-467380.php|title=Covid-19 : l\u2019unique patient en r\u00e9animation est sorti aujourd\u2019hui|language=fr|access-date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 April there are concerns about [[price gouging]], however Gilles Klaus, Director of [[Carrefour]] Matoury, denies the allegations. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/economie-consommation/la-livraison-a-domicile-seduit-les-grandes-surfaces-467316.php|title=La livraison \u00e0 domicile s\u00e9duit les grandes surfaces|language=fr|website=France-Guyane|access-date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" align=\"left\"\n|+\n'''Number of cases chronologically'''\n!Date\n!Number of cases\n!Recovered\n!Dead\n|-\n|4-7 March\n|5\n|0\n|0\n|-\n|11-12 March\n|6 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guyane.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-guyane-1-cas-secondaire-confirme-saint-laurent-du-maroni|title=Coronavirus Guyane : 1 cas \u00ab s