gency declaration by [[Mayor of New York City|Mayor]] [[Bill de Blasio]] which closes [[Broadway theatre]]s, NBC decides to record ''[[The Tonight Show with Jimmy Fallon]]'' without an audience (with a last minute appearance by Dr. [[Mehmet Oz]], plus two other previously scheduled guests), with CBS also going without an audience for ''[[The Late Show with Stephen Colbert]]'' (which instead aired footage from rehearsal with Dr. [[Sanjay Gupta]] as his sole guest after [[Maria Bamford]] canceled), while ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' only records an Internet-exclusive \"A Closer Look\" segment after that night's guests cancel. All three shows will go on hiatus starting March 16. ''Wendy'' also decides to stop taping altogether indefinitely, while [[Joy Behar]] (who, at 77, is within the 60+ age group of highest complication risk) will take a break from ''The View'' to avoid illness. The ban lasts until April 12 by order of [[Governor of New York|Governor]] [[Andrew Cuomo]] as part of a statewide emergency declaration which disallows crowds of 500 or more people.\n|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/12/business/nbc-jimmy-fallon-seth-meyers.html|title=Late-Night Shows From New York Will Go Dark Next Week|last=Koblin|first=Jon|date=12 March 2020|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/nbc-the-tonight-show-late-night-wendy-williams-show-shut-down-production-coronavirus-1202881824/|title=CBS\u2019 \u2018Late Show\u2019 Shuts Down Production Over Coronavirus, Joins NBC\u2019s \u2018The Tonight Show\u2019 & \u2018Late Night\u2019, Syndicated \u2018Wendy Williams Show\u2019 \u2013 Update|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=12 March 2020|publisher=[[Deadline.com]]|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/the-view-joy-behar-coronavirus-1203532568/|title=\u2018The View\u2019s\u2019 Joy Behar Takes Time Off Due to Coronavirus Concerns (EXCLUSI