2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=ABC takes the bait and suspends a veteran correspondent over a bad-faith, right-wing hit job|url=https://www.mediamatters.org/abc/abc-takes-bait-and-suspends-veteran-correspondent-over-bad-faith-right-wing-hit-job|author=Courtney Hagle|website=[[Media Matters for America]]|date=February 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!rowspan=3| 28\n|[[CBS Television Studios]] and [[Jerry Bruckheimer|Jerry Bruckheimer Productions]] announce a temporary suspension of production of the 33rd season of ''[[The Amazing Race (American TV series)|The Amazing Race]]'' due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]] that had [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|recently spread into Europe]]. Filming had already been completed on the season's first three episodes (which were all filmed in the [[United Kingdom]]), after which all contestants and production staff were forced to return to the United States as a precautionary measure even though none of the personnel involved experienced any signs of the coronavirus.\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/coronavirus-amazing-race-stopped-production-cbs-survivor-1202870836/|title=Coronavirus Concerns Sees \u2018The Amazing Race\u2019 Halted By CBS, For Now; \u2018Survivor\u2019 Not In Production|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|last=Patten|first=Dominic|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/cbs-suspends-amazing-race-production-coronavirus-fears-1203519026/|title=CBS Suspends \u2018The Amazing Race\u2019 Production Over Coronavirus Fears (EXCLUSIVE)|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|Telecommunications provider [[Cincinnati Bell]], which serves mainly portions of the [[Cincinnati]] area and has offered IPTV service since 2009, announces its intent to merge with [[Toronto]]-based [[Brookfield Infrastructure Partners]] for $2.75 billion in stock and cash.\n|<