A]]\n|5.1  \n|[[Telemundo]] \n|[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n|On June 27, 2019, WORA-TV announced that it will end an affiliation agreement with WKAQ-TV by December 31, leaving Telemundo without a western affiliate after more than four years. Later, Hemisphere Media Group, the owners of WAPA-TV, announced that Telemundo would air on a subchannel of WNJX-TV by January 1, 2020. On December 18, WORA-TV announced that it will move ABC programming to channel 5.1 on January 1, with the [[Televisi\u00f3n Espa\u00f1ola]] news channel [[24 Horas (Spanish TV channel)|24H]] airing on 5.2 from that date on.\n|<ref>[http://www.tvboricuausa.com/2019/12/wora-tv-apuesta-por-abc-puerto-rico-en-el-2020.html/ WORA-TV apuesta por ABC Puerto Rico en el 2020] ''TVBoricuaUSA'', December 17, 2019</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|January 28\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Harlingen, Texas|Harlingen]]/[[McAllen, Texas|McAllen]]/<br>[[Brownsville, Texas]]\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[KGBT-TV|KGBT]]\n|4.1  \n|[[CBS]]\n|Temporarily [[Silent (broadcasting)|silent]]\n|rowspan=\"5\"<!--Please change accordingly when adding/deleting a station-->|With Nexstar Media Group acquiring the non-license assets of KGBT from Sinclair Broadcast Group through the settlement of Tribune Media's 2018 lawsuit against Sinclair, Nexstar\u2014which assumed the rights to KGBT's programming and news operation\u2014decides to move KGBT's CBS schedule to a subchannel on the KVEO spectrum; the move results in KGBT ending its affiliation with CBS after 66 years and its main channel going temporarily silent until replacement programming is added. KVEO's former subchannel affiliations with Estrella TV, Court TV Mystery and Grit also move to the KGBT spectrum (on three new subchannels) to accommodate additional bandwidth needed for KVEO to transmit the former KGBT CBS programming feed on its DT2 subchannel.\n|rowspan=\"5\"|<ref>{{cite news|title=CBS 4 over-the-air programming to begin airing on KVEO Channel 23.2 Tuesday|url=https://valleycentral.com/news/local/cbs-4-over-the-air-programming-to-begin-airing-on-channel-232-tuesday|author=Ronnie Marley|website=[[KGBT-TV]]/[[KVEO-TV|KVEO-DT2]]|publisher=[[Sinclair Broadcast Group]]|date=January 27, 2020|accessdate=January 28, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Tribune/Sinclair Merger Meltdown Lawsuit Settled, To Nexstar's Benefit|url=https://www.rbr.com/tribune-sinclair-merger-meltdown-lawsuit-settled-to-nexstars-benefit/|author=Adam Jacobson|website=Radio-Television Business Report|publisher=Streamline-RBR, Inc.|date=January 28, 2020}} {{subscription required}}</ref>\n|-\n|4.4\n|New subchannel\n|[[Estrella TV]]\n|-\n|4.5\n|New subchannel\n|[[Grit (TV network)|Grit]]\n|-\n|4.6\n|New subchannel\n|[[Court TV Mystery]]\n|-\n|[[KVEO-TV|KVEO]]\n|23.2\n|Estrella TV\n|CBS\n|}\n\n====Subchannel affiliation====\n{{more citations needed|section|date=February 2020}}\n<!--Keep in chronological order-->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center; width=95px;\" |Date\n! style=\"text-align:center; width=225px;\" |Market\n! style=\"text-align:center; width:75px;\" |Station\n! style=\"text-align:center; width:30px;\" |Channel\n! style=\"text-align:center; width:225px;\" |Prior affiliation\n! style=\"text-align:center; width:225px;\" |New affiliation\n! style=\"text-align:center; width:110px;\" |Source\n|-\n| rowspan=\"21\"<!--Please change accordingly when adding/deleting a station-->|January 1 || | [[Birmingham, Alabama]] || [[WBRC]] || 6.3 || [[Grit (TV network)|Grit]] {{small|(moved to 6.5)}} || rowspan=\"8\"<!--Please change accordingly when adding/deleting a station-->|[[Circle (TV network)|Circle]] || <ref name=\"wbrc-circle\"/>\n|-\n| [[Huntsville, Alabama]] || [[WAFF (TV)|WAFF]] || 48.3 || Grit {{small|(moved to 48.5)}} || <ref name=\"waff-circle\"/>\n|-\n| [[Panama City, Florida]] || [[WECP-LD]] || 18.3 || [[Heroes & Icons]] {{small|(moved to 18.4)}} || {{citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n|-\n| [[Evansville, Indiana]] || [[WFIE]] || 14.3 || Grit {{small|