eir Deal.|date=October 31, 2019|accessdate=January 14, 2020|work=Inside Radio}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[WSYT-DT3|WNYS]]\n|43.#\n|MyNetworkTV\n|[[Syracuse, New York]]\n|The same license surrender situation occurs in Syracuse, with WSYT's license turned in, and its intellectual unit becoming the third subchannel of sister Fox affiliate [[WSYT]]. It also retains its existing virtual channels.\n|-\n|[[Vermont PBS|WVTA]]\n|41.#\n|PBS\n|[[Windsor, Vermont]]\n|TBD \n|[[Vermont PBS]] announced on February 17, 2017 that it will sell the broadcast license for WVTA, which transmits from [[Mount Ascutney]], for $56 million in the FCC spectrum auction. In a statement, the member network said that its other signals will be upgraded to cover the viewing area (southeastern [[Vermont]] and southwestern [[New Hampshire]]) served by WVTA.\n|<ref name=\"bfp-wvtasale\">{{cite news|url=http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/money/2017/02/17/vermont-pbs-sells-broadcast-licenses-56-million/98055166/|title=Vermont PBS sells broadcast licenses for $56 million|last1=Hallenbeck|first1=Brent|date=February 17, 2017|work=[[Burlington Free Press]]|accessdate=February 17, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Deaths==\n===January===\n<!--Add only people with their own articles-->\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- \"\n!width=90| Date ||width=125| Name || Age ||class=\"unsortable\" |Notability || class=\"unsortable\" | Source\n|-\n|rowspan=2| January 1\n|[[David Stern]]\n|77\n|Commissioner of the [[National Basketball Association]] from 1984\u20132014 who oversaw the launches of [[NBA TV]] and [[NBA League Pass]].\n|<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/01/sports/basketball/david-stern-dead.html|title = David Stern, Transformative N.B.A. Leader, Dies at 77|work = [[The New York Times]]|date = January 1, 2020|accessdate = January 1, 2020|last = Stein|first = Marc}}</ref>\n|-\n|Barry ZeVan\n|82\n|American television weathercaster at [[Minneapolis\u2013St. Paul]] stations [[KARE (TV)|KARE]] and [[KSTP-TV]] and [[Wash